00:22:38.980 --> 00:22:48.190
So science-- science evolved
as a way of understanding

00:22:48.190 --> 00:22:48.950
the natural world.

00:22:48.950 --> 00:22:51.220
It came out of
natural philosophy.

00:22:51.220 --> 00:22:56.410
It's an 18th/19th century
kind of conceptual framework.

00:22:56.410 --> 00:23:00.400
It is observational at heart.

00:23:00.400 --> 00:23:03.250
It observes the natural
world, and attempts

00:23:03.250 --> 00:23:06.580
to understand how
it's put together.

00:23:06.580 --> 00:23:09.070
And it's organized
around discovery

00:23:09.070 --> 00:23:12.010
about that natural
world and its order.

00:23:12.010 --> 00:23:15.100
Technology is really different.

00:23:15.100 --> 00:23:18.340
It is a system to organize
scientific and technical

00:23:18.340 --> 00:23:23.920
knowledge to go after a
more practical purpose.

00:23:23.920 --> 00:23:28.987
And this systems includes the
technical advance plus models

00:23:28.987 --> 00:23:30.070
to implement that advance.

00:23:30.070 --> 00:23:36.760
So you move from observation
to implementation.

00:23:36.760 --> 00:23:38.980
And this is, obviously,
the historical boundary

00:23:38.980 --> 00:23:42.580
between science and engineering.

00:23:42.580 --> 00:23:48.580
And research-- another
term we'll use constantly--

00:23:48.580 --> 00:23:56.720
means increasing the scientific
or technical knowledge or both.

00:23:56.720 --> 00:24:01.850
So research can pursue either
of these historic ends, or both

00:24:01.850 --> 00:24:04.100
simultaneously.

00:24:04.100 --> 00:24:09.230
Invention is about applying
research knowledge to create

00:24:09.230 --> 00:24:10.880
a practical idea or device.

00:24:14.890 --> 00:24:19.150
Invention is really
different than innovation.

00:24:19.150 --> 00:24:22.330
Innovation is built on
scientific discovery

00:24:22.330 --> 00:24:27.040
and on breakthrough
invention or inventions,

00:24:27.040 --> 00:24:31.330
but it is the system of research
invention development that

00:24:31.330 --> 00:24:34.630
uses both scientific
background, scientific knowledge

00:24:34.630 --> 00:24:38.260
and technology knowledge to
lead to the implementation

00:24:38.260 --> 00:24:44.470
and widespread applicability
of a technology area.

00:24:44.470 --> 00:24:48.580
So typically, in our society,
that means commercialization.

00:24:48.580 --> 00:24:52.150
So this class is about this.

00:24:52.150 --> 00:24:54.550
That's the stage
we're most focused on.

00:24:54.550 --> 00:24:58.390
But remember all the input
above that that goes into this.

00:25:01.180 --> 00:25:03.640
Now, an innovation system--
we talked about this briefly

00:25:03.640 --> 00:25:04.720
before--

00:25:04.720 --> 00:25:07.270
is the ecosystem for
developing innovation.

00:25:07.270 --> 00:25:12.250
And as we discussed, briefly,
it operates at least two levels.

00:25:12.250 --> 00:25:15.010
It operates at the
institutional level

00:25:15.010 --> 00:25:18.880
of supporting the development
of the inventions and discovery

00:25:18.880 --> 00:25:21.550
that go into
innovation, but it also

00:25:21.550 --> 00:25:25.060
operates at the personal,
face-to-face level.

00:25:25.060 --> 00:25:27.610
Because in the end, people--

00:25:27.610 --> 00:25:30.905
you all-- innovate, not
some fancy institution.

00:25:33.580 --> 00:25:36.880
Innovation wave
theory-- in economics,

00:25:36.880 --> 00:25:39.430
this is called
Kondratiev theory.

00:25:39.430 --> 00:25:48.180
And we'll talk more about
this as the class goes on.

00:25:48.180 --> 00:25:50.220
But let me just give kind
of a snapshot of what

00:25:50.220 --> 00:25:52.380
I'm talking about.

00:25:52.380 --> 00:25:54.390
Innovation tends
to come in a wave.

00:25:54.390 --> 00:25:57.000
And in your lifetime,
the big wave

00:25:57.000 --> 00:26:00.390
has been the IT revolution.

00:26:00.390 --> 00:26:04.260
If we were born
in 1800, railroads

00:26:04.260 --> 00:26:06.510
would be like a big
innovation wave.

00:26:06.510 --> 00:26:09.150
Early telegraph-based
communication

00:26:09.150 --> 00:26:11.490
would be a big innovation wave.

00:26:11.490 --> 00:26:15.120
Electricity would be
a big innovation wave.

00:26:15.120 --> 00:26:18.900
And you tend to have a
core technology advance,

00:26:18.900 --> 00:26:21.960
you pile on applications,
and it begins

00:26:21.960 --> 00:26:24.277
to move through
an entire society

00:26:24.277 --> 00:26:25.485
and affect the whole society.

00:26:28.830 --> 00:26:31.440
And to some extent,
the technology

00:26:31.440 --> 00:26:33.930
drives the nature
of the society.

00:26:33.930 --> 00:26:35.550
So that's what
Karl Marx believed.

00:26:35.550 --> 00:26:39.180
That's called determinism,
that the technology

00:26:39.180 --> 00:26:42.790
plays a deterministic role in
the organization of society.

00:26:42.790 --> 00:26:45.630
So it's big.

00:26:45.630 --> 00:26:46.770
It is very big.

00:26:46.770 --> 00:26:48.758
It's not just a pile of
new technology stuff,

00:26:48.758 --> 00:26:51.300
and it's fundamentally changing
the way in which this society

00:26:51.300 --> 00:26:52.200
is organized as well.

00:26:52.200 --> 00:26:54.320
So that's also part of
these innovation waves.

00:26:57.480 --> 00:27:00.540
So a wave hits an
economy, takes a long time

00:27:00.540 --> 00:27:03.540
to grow, eventually
it scales up,

00:27:03.540 --> 00:27:08.130
and affects a good part of
the economy at any given time.

00:27:08.130 --> 00:27:11.130
Eventually, you run out
of the technology menu,

00:27:11.130 --> 00:27:13.440
and it stabilizes.

00:27:13.440 --> 00:27:15.960
But it doesn't disappear,
it creates a new plateau

00:27:15.960 --> 00:27:17.310
in your economy.

00:27:17.310 --> 00:27:19.070
And then you do another wave.

00:27:19.070 --> 00:27:19.570
Yeah.

