that any organization can apply
to, if they're public, private,

01:20:05.774 --> 01:20:06.274
etc.

01:20:08.860 --> 01:20:13.078
And what we, as a society, value
and how we brand that value

01:20:13.078 --> 01:20:14.620
and make it appealing
and interesting

01:20:14.620 --> 01:20:18.723
to the regular consumer
is of great concern to me,

01:20:18.723 --> 01:20:20.140
especially, because
science is not

01:20:20.140 --> 01:20:23.898
something that's accessible
or exciting to most people.

01:20:23.898 --> 01:20:24.940
WILLIAM BONVILLIAN: Yeah.

01:20:24.940 --> 01:20:27.160
[INAUDIBLE],, you're
right on a whole series

01:20:27.160 --> 01:20:30.430
of big important
problems that we

01:20:30.430 --> 01:20:34.780
need to keep bringing into
this class discussion.

01:20:34.780 --> 01:20:38.230
And creating a
culture around science

01:20:38.230 --> 01:20:40.650
and creating culture around
technology and development,

01:20:40.650 --> 01:20:42.250
a culture around
entrepreneurship,

01:20:42.250 --> 01:20:44.590
and a culture around
startups, those

01:20:44.590 --> 01:20:47.680
turn out to be fairly key.

01:20:47.680 --> 01:20:49.660
It's hard for
economics that's trying

01:20:49.660 --> 01:20:51.820
to do mathematical
modeling to capture

01:20:51.820 --> 01:20:56.950
these cultural,
historical issues.

01:20:56.950 --> 01:20:58.390
But they're there.

01:20:58.390 --> 01:21:02.200
And you know, part of what
makes innovation systems theory

01:21:02.200 --> 01:21:05.050
so interesting is just the
sheer complexity of that system

01:21:05.050 --> 01:21:07.570
and the number of
variables operating there.

01:21:07.570 --> 01:21:11.620
And you're right on
an important point.

01:21:14.330 --> 01:21:17.420
Understanding the historical
context, for example,

01:21:17.420 --> 01:21:21.440
turns out to be pretty key when
you look at innovation systems

01:21:21.440 --> 01:21:23.360
in different regions
of the world, right?

01:21:23.360 --> 01:21:26.510
Different regions have different
ways of organizing innovation

01:21:26.510 --> 01:21:27.560
systems.

01:21:27.560 --> 01:21:29.690
The innovation system that
got organized in Japan,

01:21:29.690 --> 01:21:31.490
coming out of the
Second World War

01:21:31.490 --> 01:21:35.623
is a very different innovation
system than the US organized.

01:21:35.623 --> 01:21:37.790
And we'll try and talk about
some of that, actually,

01:21:37.790 --> 01:21:39.270
in the next class.

01:21:39.270 --> 01:21:42.650
